The political uncertainty arising from last year’s contested elections has finally been contained after President Uhuru Kenyatta and NASA leader Raila Odinga held a surprise meeting and resolved to end their differences and embrace dialogue for the country’s posterity. In a symbolic joint address to the nation from the staircase of the President’s Harambee House Office, the two leaders agreed to work together in tackling the challenges facing the country including corruption, security, exclusivity and institutional reforms. 